==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shyness
<hw>Shy"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or state of being
shy.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>shiness</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Frequency in heavenly contemplation is particularly important to
prevent a <qex>shyness</qex> bewtween God and thy soul.</q>
<rj><qau>Baxter.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Bashfulness; reserve; coyness; timidity;
diffidence. See <er>Bashfulness</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shyster</ent>⟦br⟧
